## Simple Returns ##

Let $$P_t$$ denote the price in month $$t$$ of an asset that pays no dividends and let $$P_{t−1}$$ denote the price in month $$t − 1$$.

$$R = \frac{(P_t - P_{t-1})}{P_{t-1}}$$

## Continuously Compounded Returns ##

Let $$P_t$$ denote the price in month $$t$$ of an asset that pays no dividends and let $$P_{t−1}$$ denote the price in month $$t − 1$$.

$$r = \ln\left(\frac{P_t}{P_{t-1}}\right)$$
